# React UI Components

## Component Structure

- Use functional components with hooks; avoid class components.
- Keep component responsibilities focused (container vs presentational).
- Prefer existing helpers like `classNames()` from `src/utils/helpers.js` for dynamic classes.
- Use shared constants from `src/utils/constants.js` for statuses, priorities, and columns.
- Keep routing in `src/App.jsx`; add new pages under `src/pages/` and reusable UI in `src/components/`.
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes and shared styles (`btn-primary`, `input-field`, `card`) over inline styles.

## Loading States

Always show loading indicators for async operations:

```jsx
// Button with loading state
<button
  type="submit"
  disabled={isSubmitting}
  className="btn-primary disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed flex items-center gap-2"
>
  {isSubmitting && (
    <svg className="animate-spin h-4 w-4" ...>
      {/* Spinner SVG */}
    </svg>
  )}
  {isSubmitting ? "Updating..." : "Update"}
</button>

// Full-screen overlay for forms
{isSubmitting && (
  <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-dark-900/50 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-lg z-10 flex items-center justify-center">
    <div className="flex flex-col items-center gap-3">
      <div className="inline-block w-12 h-12 border-4 border-primary-600 border-t-transparent rounded-full animate-spin"></div>
      <p className="text-dark-200 font-medium">Processing...</p>
    </div>
  </div>
)}
```

**Best practices**:

- Disable all interactive elements during submission
- Show spinner + descriptive text
- Use overlay for forms to prevent interaction
- Keep loading messages clear and specific

## Toast Notifications

Use `useToastStore` for user feedback:

```jsx
import { useToastStore } from "../stores/toastStore";

const { showToast } = useToastStore();

// Success
showToast("Task updated successfully", "success");

// Error
showToast("Failed to save task", "error");

// Info
showToast("Processing your request", "info");
```

**When to use toasts**:

- After successful mutations (create, update, delete)
- After failed operations (show error message)
- For important notifications that don't require action
- Auto-dismiss after 3 seconds (default)

**Don't use toasts for**:

- Validation errors (show inline)
- Confirmations (use dialogs)
- Critical errors (use error boundaries)

## Lazy Loading Pattern

Load data only when needed, not upfront:

```jsx
// Track loaded state
const [dataLoaded, setDataLoaded] = useState(false);
const [data, setData] = useState([]);

// Load function with caching
const loadData = async () => {
  if (dataLoaded) return; // Don't reload
  
  setLoading(true);
  try {
    const result = await fetchData();
    setData(result);
    setDataLoaded(true);
  } finally {
    setLoading(false);
  }
};

// Trigger on tab click or user action
<Tab.Group onChange={(index) => {
  if (index === 1 && !dataLoaded) {
    loadData();
  }
}}>
```

**Best practices**:

- Use flags to track loaded state
- Cache data after first load
- Invalidate cache after mutations
- Show loading state while fetching

## Modal Patterns

For modals with multiple tabs:

```jsx
const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState(0);
const [historyLoaded, setHistoryLoaded] = useState(false);

// Reset on modal open
useEffect(() => {
  if (isOpen) {
    setActiveTab(0);
    setHistoryLoaded(false);
  }
}, [isOpen]);

// Lazy load on tab change
const handleTabChange = (index) => {
  setActiveTab(index);
  if (index === 1 && !historyLoaded) {
    loadHistory();
  }
};
```

## Form Submission

Prevent double-submission and show progress:

```jsx
const [isSubmitting, setIsSubmitting] = useState(false);

const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  
  // Prevent double submission
  if (isSubmitting) return;
  
  setIsSubmitting(true);
  
  try {
    await saveData();
    showToast("Saved successfully", "success");
  } catch (error) {
    showToast(error.message, "error");
  } finally {
    setIsSubmitting(false);
  }
};
```
